OL,3,CThames Water funding woes deepen after
OL,4,Cshareholders pull investment plan
OL,6,FBut it is understood that Ofwat has
OL,7,Frefused to bow to the water giant's
OL,8,Fdemands for concessions, said to
OL,9,Finclude a 40% bill hike for customers,
OL,10,Fan easing of capital spending
OL,11,Frequirements as well as leniency on
OL,12,Fregulatory penalties.
OL,14,FChris Weston, chief executive of
OL,15,FThames Water, said: "I'd like to
OL,16,Freassure our customers that, despite
OL,17,Fthis announcement, it is business as
OL,18,Fusual for Thames Water.
